227
01:32:23.947 --> 01:32:26.780
And... sold to the lady
on the left.

228
01:32:26.983 --> 01:32:31.750
The last sale of the evening. lot
number 72 on the turntable there...

229
01:32:31.955 --> 01:32:34.719
and star of the night...
Where is she?

230
01:32:34.925 --> 01:32:38.918
The last violin
of Nicolo Bussotti. 1681.

231
01:32:39.129 --> 01:32:41.324
-A masterpiece of the Golden Age.
-Do you see it?

232
01:32:41.531 --> 01:32:44.591
-No. not yet.
-If she will give us the pleasure.

233
01:32:46.636 --> 01:32:53.166
And here she is now. lot number 72.
the so-called ''Red Violin''.

234
01:32:53.643 --> 01:32:58.808
-It's not how I remember it.
-They've cleaned it up. It's better.

235
01:32:59.182 --> 01:33:01.480
US$ 260.000.
Good evening. Mr. Ruselsky.

236
01:33:02.385 --> 01:33:05.183
-US$ 270.000. Suzanne on the phone.
-Maybe if I heard it again.

237
01:33:05.388 --> 01:33:08.824
US$ 280.000. Back to you. Sir.
US$ 300.000 at the back of the hall.

238
01:33:09.025 --> 01:33:14.554
US$ 320.000. Suzanne. I see you.
340. I have you. 380. Mr. Ruselsky.

239
01:35:16.252 --> 01:35:18.914
-And how was your flight?
-Very good. On time.

240
01:35:19.122 --> 01:35:22.819
-Sorry to cut your holiday short. but...
-It's all right. I'm excited. actually.

241
01:35:23.026 --> 01:35:24.926
-Like Christmas.
-Won't take too long.

242
01:35:25.128 --> 01:35:28.154
-We've already assessed them.
-Right. Ballpark.

243
01:35:28.365 --> 01:35:30.526
-And I only want you to confirm it.
-I got it.

244
01:35:30.734 --> 01:35:33.760
-A second opinion.
-I've done this sort of thing before.

245
01:35:33.970 --> 01:35:35.665
Can't wait to see it. actually.

246
01:35:38.108 --> 01:35:41.043
-This is Mr. Morritz. you know...
-Bon jour.

247
01:35:42.445 --> 01:35:45.937
-So. you're the expert?
-From New York.

248
01:35:47.017 --> 01:35:51.181
-You know what you're doing?
-Yes. New York.

249
01:35:51.721 --> 01:35:56.249
-You know what you're doing?
-Why. yes. I certainly hope so.

250
01:35:56.459 --> 01:35:58.984
These people from Duval's
have given us some figures...

251
01:35:59.195 --> 01:36:01.527
as the government of China.

252
01:36:02.632 --> 01:36:05.999
-So. what we need now is...
-A professional opinion.

253
01:36:06.536 --> 01:36:10.495
-No. a signed affidavit.
-That's what I'm here for.

254
01:36:10.707 --> 01:36:14.143
-Show me to the Strad.
-They all look the same to me.

255
01:36:14.344 --> 01:36:17.643
Ah. but they're not.
Please don't let me forget this.

256
01:36:17.847 --> 01:36:19.405
Over there.

257
01:36:26.389 --> 01:36:30.587
Ah. here she is.
It's a beautiful specimen.

258
01:36:34.264 --> 01:36:38.758
I'd say about... 1683.

259
01:36:39.969 --> 01:36:43.996
-Reminds me of the Cobbitt.
-These are the best quality pieces.

260
01:36:44.207 --> 01:36:47.870
Over here. if you'd like
to take a look...

261
01:36:48.078 --> 01:36:51.445
are the Iess promising entries.
some of them are pretty bad.

262
01:36:54.050 --> 01:36:58.248
-So I see.
-So. I guess I'll leave it to you then.

263
01:36:58.455 --> 01:37:02.255
I've taken care of the luggage.
I have a driver waiting.

264
01:37:02.826 --> 01:37:04.851
All right. I shouldn't be long.

265
01:37:37.727 --> 01:37:39.661
-Bon jour.
-Bon jour. Monsieur Morritz.

266
01:37:39.863 --> 01:37:43.390
-Everything is ready as you asked for.
-Same room as always?

267
01:37:43.600 --> 01:37:47.866
-Same room. but one story down.
-Then it's not the same room. is it?

268
01:37:48.071 --> 01:37:50.539
No. Sir. but it's the same
as the other one.

269
01:37:50.740 --> 01:37:54.676
-Sir. I have a message from your wife.
-Merci.

270
01:38:05.889 --> 01:38:07.857
Room 2.703.

271
01:38:08.725 --> 01:38:10.454
New York City. please.

272
01:38:11.561 --> 01:38:14.189
316-2799.

273
01:38:17.934 --> 01:38:23.304
Carrie? CharIes Morritz here.
I have a little gumshoe work for you.

274
01:38:23.506 --> 01:38:27.033
Cremona. Bussotti.
Get a pen.

275
01:38:33.283 --> 01:38:36.582
Made a cast of this
after we set the tabIe.

276
01:38:37.587 --> 01:38:39.316
Swiss.

277
01:38:39.522 --> 01:38:42.514
So. here we are.
Here's the before picture.

278
01:38:42.859 --> 01:38:46.192
Take a look at the corners. Not so bad.
I don't think we have to touch them.

279
01:38:46.396 --> 01:38:49.888
Some really nice perfling here.

280
01:38:51.034 --> 01:38:53.002
Lot of work to get it this far.

281
01:38:53.203 --> 01:38:56.229
Turn-of-the-century hackjob
with some horse glue and a patch...

282
01:38:56.439 --> 01:38:58.737
so I had to reset the neck.
That was the big job.

283
01:38:59.008 --> 01:39:01.704
Sound post. taiI piece.
New bridge. of course.

284
01:39:02.145 --> 01:39:06.946
But the body itself is remarkably good.
so I'll strip back some varnish here...

285
01:39:07.350 --> 01:39:09.944
-No. no. no.
-No what?

286
01:39:10.186 --> 01:39:13.417
I told you before.
Don't touch the varnish.

287
01:39:13.890 --> 01:39:17.690
-Well. that's not gonna be easy.
-If there's a probIem. I'll do it.

288
01:39:20.330 --> 01:39:23.458
Look. the auction's in two weeks.
I have 16 other instruments.

289
01:39:23.666 --> 01:39:26.897
Leroux is all over my ass. I still have
a Stein I haven't even touched...

290
01:39:27.103 --> 01:39:30.436
I want complete L.I.G.'s.
a resonance test. mass specs...

291
01:39:30.640 --> 01:39:33.905
and let's get some varnish samples
off to the lab. okay?

292
01:39:36.312 --> 01:39:41.079
This instrument is not a priority.
Every minute of my day is full.

293
01:39:41.284 --> 01:39:45.516
That's fine. We'll do this
after hours. all right?

294
01:39:53.062 --> 01:39:56.156
-These are the estimates?
-No. the reserves.

295
01:39:56.366 --> 01:39:59.096
-That we proposed to the Chinese?
-Right.

296
01:40:00.236 --> 01:40:02.033
And what about these?

297
01:40:02.238 --> 01:40:05.969
Those are some contentious items
you might not want to put on the block.

298
01:40:06.175 --> 01:40:09.042
They're badIy preserved
and hard to attribute.

299
01:40:09.879 --> 01:40:13.246
-What about that red one?
-Red one?

300
01:40:13.483 --> 01:40:16.247
Leroux seemed to think
it might be a Bussotti.

301
01:40:18.288 --> 01:40:19.812
Yes.

302
01:40:20.623 --> 01:40:24.957
It might be. but the label's obscured
and the varnish is odd...

303
01:40:25.161 --> 01:40:29.928
it's slightly opaque. And I'm afraid
as it stands. with no documentation...

304
01:40:30.667 --> 01:40:33.431
That's all you expect?

305
01:40:50.520 --> 01:40:56.789
''With all my heart''.

306
01:40:59.262 --> 01:41:02.527
You ever heard of the Red Violin?

307
01:41:02.732 --> 01:41:09.160
Sure. The Frederick Pope Bussotti?
Sure. I have. stories.

308
01:41:09.372 --> 01:41:12.808
-How about copies?
-One in London. the only one I know of.

309
01:41:13.009 --> 01:41:16.172
Supposed to be a copy
commissioned by Pope.

310
01:41:16.379 --> 01:41:19.871
-You know who has it?
-Some private collection.

311
01:41:21.150 --> 01:41:25.314
You think I could buy it
without tipping them off?

312
01:41:26.055 --> 01:41:28.455
Tipping them off to what?

313
01:41:28.658 --> 01:41:32.116
Well. we know for sure we have a
Bussotti. I can date it within the year.

314
01:41:32.328 --> 01:41:35.229
We still have this varnish
that doesn't configure. but...

315
01:41:35.431 --> 01:41:40.391
but we can run comparison tests and
see if this is the source of the copy.

316
01:41:43.172 --> 01:41:46.664
You know I should probably
tell my empIoyer.

317
01:41:46.876 --> 01:41:52.246
If what you're saying is any way true.
people could get a little... excited.

318
01:41:52.448 --> 01:41:56.214
-I could Iose my job over this.
-Yes. I know.

319
01:41:57.820 --> 01:42:02.280
You can go if you want to.
I can finish this myself.

320
01:42:26.349 --> 01:42:29.978
Madame Leroux says that she has
to have the catalog proofs for today.

321
01:42:31.888 --> 01:42:36.257
-Are you finished?
-Yes. they're back at my hotel.

322
01:42:36.459 --> 01:42:38.256
I've been working at night.

323
01:42:41.030 --> 01:42:42.827
Is there something else?

324
01:42:45.768 --> 01:42:47.929
Your wife called again.

325
01:42:49.205 --> 01:42:51.400
Close the door. please.

326
01:43:01.250 --> 01:43:03.582
Yes. is this the University of Montreal?

327
01:43:04.220 --> 01:43:06.882
Well. may I have the
Archaeology department. please?

328
01:43:10.993 --> 01:43:14.156
Hi. This is CharIes Morritz
over at Duval's.

329
01:43:14.363 --> 01:43:17.298
I sent you some varnish samples
on Tuesday.

330
01:43:18.901 --> 01:43:22.393
Yeah. I wanted you to
isolate an organic compound.

331
01:44:00.409 --> 01:44:02.377
I'm sorry.

332
01:44:07.917 --> 01:44:09.714
Can I have the manager. please?

333
01:44:10.486 --> 01:44:14.582
Yes. the manager.
Well. fine. put him on.

334
01:44:16.726 --> 01:44:19.854
Yes. this is Mr. Morritz in 2.703.

335
01:44:20.062 --> 01:44:23.054
Listen. I want to make
something absolutely clear.

336
01:44:23.266 --> 01:44:26.429
I don't want anyone coming
to my room. You understand?

337
01:44:26.636 --> 01:44:31.130
Not the maid. not to check the minibar.
no chocolates on the pillow.

338
01:44:31.340 --> 01:44:34.741
I'm giving the staff sort of a break.
Understand?

339
01:44:34.944 --> 01:44:39.506
No one is to come in my room
unless I request it.

340
01:44:40.550 --> 01:44:42.074
Thank you.

341
01:45:02.805 --> 01:45:04.966
-Yes?
-I got it.

342
01:45:05.174 --> 01:45:08.200
It's coming.
I just talked to London.

343
01:45:08.411 --> 01:45:12.677
Well. a little bit of smooth talking.
a little bit more money. Your money.

344
01:45:14.383 --> 01:45:16.544
You better make those phone calls.

345
01:45:17.853 --> 01:45:20.117
Yeah. yeah. Me too.

346
01:45:21.023 --> 01:45:22.854
Well. actually. I had some ideas.

347
01:45:37.106 --> 01:45:38.835
-Wonderful.
-Yes.

348
01:45:39.041 --> 01:45:43.034
I have the recording.
Pretty good Strad. don't you think?

349
01:45:43.245 --> 01:45:45.440
I feel it is a bit tight on the top.

350
01:45:45.648 --> 01:45:48.446
A little bit strangled over the break.

351
01:45:48.651 --> 01:45:51.779
To me it's very clean and precise.

352
01:45:51.988 --> 01:45:54.821
Of course. it would have
to be played by a master.

353
01:45:55.825 --> 01:45:59.989
-What do you guess?
-US$ 1.7... 1.8 million.

354
01:46:00.196 --> 01:46:02.255
-Not bad.
-Trust me on this.

355
01:46:02.465 --> 01:46:06.367
-What else do you have?
-That's about it. Thanks for coming.

356
01:46:06.569 --> 01:46:08.628
I hope you don't have
an orchestra waiting.

357
01:46:08.838 --> 01:46:11.830
Well. they can wait. No probIem.

358
01:46:14.410 --> 01:46:16.742
What about this here?

359
01:46:17.079 --> 01:46:19.047
No. not that one.

360
01:46:20.082 --> 01:46:23.882
-Nice little piece.
-But not for you.

361
01:46:25.521 --> 01:46:28.319
-I will try it.
-No. no. no. Don't play it.

362
01:46:28.524 --> 01:46:30.685
-Why not?
-Yes. why not?

363
01:46:30.893 --> 01:46:35.455
I just repaired it. It's still fragiIe.
I don't even know why it's here.

364
01:46:35.665 --> 01:46:38.793
I'll be very gentle.
Don't worry.

365
01:47:31.887 --> 01:47:36.551
Yes. I see what you mean.
Nothing special.

366
01:47:45.501 --> 01:47:47.230
How's it going?

367
01:47:49.705 --> 01:47:53.197
What do you want me to do
with that one... the Pope copy?

368
01:47:53.409 --> 01:47:55.969
I'll take it back to the hotel with me.

369
01:47:56.178 --> 01:48:01.480
Well. you got your money's worth.
That is a very good copy. Nice violin.

370
01:48:02.084 --> 01:48:04.780
But nothing like this one.

371
01:48:04.987 --> 01:48:09.651
This is the single most perfect
acoustic machine...

372
01:48:09.992 --> 01:48:12.460
I have ever seen.

373
01:48:14.764 --> 01:48:16.459
Amazing.

374
01:48:26.542 --> 01:48:29.204
Guess I never thought I'd find it.

375
01:48:32.948 --> 01:48:36.577
The ultimate... thing. as I see it.

376
01:48:38.654 --> 01:48:44.058
The perfect marriage of
science and beauty.

377
01:48:46.395 --> 01:48:48.158
ImpossibIe thing.

378
01:48:50.800 --> 01:48:52.495
Now what?

379
01:48:53.636 --> 01:48:59.302
What do you do when the thing
you've most wanted. so... perfect...

380
01:49:00.476 --> 01:49:02.569
just comes?

381
01:49:09.185 --> 01:49:12.052
-Do you have children?
-What?

382
01:49:12.254 --> 01:49:17.021
-ChiIdren. Do you have any?
-No. but I know what you mean.

383
01:49:17.226 --> 01:49:20.024
I would Iove to have
this baby for myself.

384
01:49:20.696 --> 01:49:23.927
Really? What would you do?

385
01:49:25.000 --> 01:49:28.197
Take it apart. find out how it works.

386
01:49:28.404 --> 01:49:31.737
Take some Eigenbaud readings
on the individual plates...

387
01:49:31.941 --> 01:49:37.641
-I don't think you get it.
-Yes. I do. Take a look at this.

388
01:49:38.414 --> 01:49:44.284
This is mode 1.06 kHz.
Watch the response curve here.

389
01:49:49.058 --> 01:49:51.720
I'll ease it up sIowIy for you.

390
01:49:56.966 --> 01:49:59.127
Mode 2...

391
01:50:03.906 --> 01:50:05.464
Stop it!

392
01:50:11.146 --> 01:50:12.841
-Bon jour. Monsieur Morritz.
-Bon jour.

393
01:50:13.048 --> 01:50:16.779
Oh. and I have an envelope for you
from University of Montreal.

394
01:50:18.787 --> 01:50:21.654
This says this arrived at 7 o'clock.
I was in my room.

395
01:50:21.857 --> 01:50:24.485
-Yes. Sir.
-Well. why wasn't I notified?

396
01:50:24.793 --> 01:50:28.388
-Sir. you told us not to disturb you.
-Not for a courier.

397
01:50:28.597 --> 01:50:31.327
-I didn't know. Sir.
-If a courier comes. you call me.

398
01:50:31.533 --> 01:50:34.127
-If a fax comes. you call me.
-Yes.

399
01:50:34.336 --> 01:50:39.569
It's important. You get it? You knock
on my door and you put it in my hand!

400
01:50:40.309 --> 01:50:43.710
-I need you to acknowIedge.
-Yes.

401
01:50:47.750 --> 01:50:50.218
This is my business!

402
01:54:34.576 --> 01:54:40.276
Mr. Morritz. I'm sorry. You'd better
come up. They're waiting for you.

403
01:54:40.482 --> 01:54:42.382
All right.

404
01:54:46.555 --> 01:54:50.889
So nice of you to join us. I hope you
don't mind us starting without you...

405
01:54:51.093 --> 01:54:55.029
but there was the question of unusual
expenses. both here in the office...

406
01:54:55.230 --> 01:54:58.199
and at the hotel.

407
01:54:58.400 --> 01:55:01.631
-Did you check my mini-bar too?
-It is our card. We are paying.

408
01:55:01.837 --> 01:55:05.796
You made me wonder. so we decided
to come down and have a look.

409
01:55:06.008 --> 01:55:07.873
And my... you have been busy.

410
01:55:08.243 --> 01:55:12.179
With the courier bills and DNA tests...

411
01:55:12.381 --> 01:55:16.147
Very curious procedures.
Leroux has a theory.

412
01:55:16.485 --> 01:55:18.419
Tell me if she's wrong.

413
01:55:23.525 --> 01:55:28.986
Is our little red violin
the Red Violin?

414
01:55:35.938 --> 01:55:40.341
Yes. I just wanted to be
sure before I told you.

415
01:55:40.542 --> 01:55:46.037
-This is very good news.
-I'll send off the press release.

416
01:55:50.085 --> 01:55:53.577
Good work. Thank you.

417
01:55:54.289 --> 01:55:58.248
Why don't you take these last
few days off... before you go home?

418
01:56:06.401 --> 01:56:08.961
No. I won't forget!

419
01:56:09.972 --> 01:56:12.566
He lied!
He lied to me!

420
01:56:12.774 --> 01:56:17.711
And I knew it as soon as I saw it.
And I said it.

421
01:56:18.981 --> 01:56:22.246
This instrument should be mine.

422
01:56:23.986 --> 01:56:25.613
Son of a bitch!

423
01:56:26.722 --> 01:56:28.121
63...

424
01:56:29.725 --> 01:56:31.249
56...

425
01:56:33.228 --> 01:56:34.559
51...

426
01:57:22.744 --> 01:57:25.110
Ladies and gentlemen. Duval's...

427
01:57:25.314 --> 01:57:28.442
would like to welcome
you to this awaited evening.

428
01:57:28.650 --> 01:57:32.086
Our thanks
to the government of China...

429
01:57:32.287 --> 01:57:35.518
for entrusting us with this
marvelous collection.

430
01:57:35.724 --> 01:57:38.318
Thanks too to Madame Leroux...

431
01:57:38.527 --> 01:57:41.928
who organized and made
possibIe this auction.

432
01:57:42.130 --> 01:57:45.463
Let me remind you that
the conditions of sale...

433
01:57:45.667 --> 01:57:47.430
are Iisted in the catalog.

434
01:57:47.636 --> 01:57:51.367
Before we begin. it is my duty to
direct you to the conditions of sale...

435
01:57:51.573 --> 01:57:53.666
that you'll find at the front
of the catalog.

436
01:57:53.875 --> 01:57:58.107
I will not read them out Ioud at this
point but consider yourselves warned.

437
01:57:59.614 --> 01:58:03.243
Now. we'll begin with lot number one.
showing on the turntabIe on my right...

438
01:58:03.685 --> 01:58:08.918
a fine French cello.
And we'll start with US$ 10.000.

439
01:58:09.124 --> 01:58:11.115
US$ 10.000.

440
01:58:40.288 --> 01:58:42.415
-Anything else?
-No.

441
01:58:42.891 --> 01:58:45.223
-Which airport. Sir?
-Dorval.

442
01:58:50.966 --> 01:58:53.560
There is one stop we have to make.

443
01:58:56.338 --> 01:59:00.331
US$ 400.000 at the back of the room.
The Stradivarius now at US$ 400.000.

444
01:59:00.542 --> 01:59:03.272
Against the telephone US$ 420.
US$ 450.000.

445
01:59:03.578 --> 01:59:08.743
Against you. Sir.
US$ 500 back to the front. US$ 500.

446
01:59:09.618 --> 01:59:13.019
-Wait here. I'll just be a minute.
-I might have to go around the block.

447
01:59:13.221 --> 01:59:15.280
All right. if you have to.

448
01:59:22.197 --> 01:59:26.657
US$ 1.100 million. US$ 1.100...
US$ 1.200 million.

449
01:59:26.935 --> 01:59:29.403
Is that a bid. Sir? Don't be shy.
All right. then I'll take it.

450
01:59:29.604 --> 01:59:32.698
US$ 1.300 million.
US$ 1.400...

451
01:59:32.908 --> 01:59:36.503
1.500. Yes. Sir. I've got you.
US$ 1.600 million.

452
01:59:36.711 --> 01:59:40.044
US$ 1.600 million.
Not you. Sir? US$ 1.650 million.

453
01:59:40.515 --> 01:59:42.415
US$ 1.675 million.

454
01:59:43.385 --> 01:59:46.786
-M. Morritz.
-Please don't let me forget this.

455
01:59:47.222 --> 01:59:49.656
Against the telephone now.
Against you. Sir.

456
01:59:49.858 --> 01:59:53.123
US$ 1.810 million.
US$ 1.850.

457
01:59:53.328 --> 01:59:55.819
US$ 1.875 million in the room.

458
01:59:56.031 --> 01:59:59.762
US$ 1.900?
US$ 1.900 million.

459
02:00:00.168 --> 02:00:03.968
US$ 1.900 million on the telephone.
US$ 1.920 in the room.

460
02:00:04.172 --> 02:00:07.938
I've got you. Sir. Thank you.
US$ 1.940 million.

461
02:00:08.143 --> 02:00:10.976
Not yours. ma'am.
Neither of yours.

462
02:00:11.179 --> 02:00:14.205
US$ 1.940 million.

463
02:00:14.816 --> 02:00:18.047
-Son of a bitch.
-I'll take ten.

464
02:00:18.253 --> 02:00:22.087
Do you want back in. Sir?
Is that a yes? No?

465
02:00:22.290 --> 02:00:25.384
The Stradivarius now
at US$ 1.940 million.

466
02:00:26.127 --> 02:00:28.755
Not yours. ma'am.
Neither of yours.

467
02:00:28.964 --> 02:00:33.333
US$ 1.940 million.
Against you all in the room.

468
02:00:33.535 --> 02:00:37.027
Is that all. then?
Fair warning.

469
02:00:37.239 --> 02:00:39.901
US$ 1.950 million on my left.
Down to you two now.

470
02:00:40.108 --> 02:00:45.068
US$ 1.950 million.
Not yours. Sir. Not yours. Paul.

471
02:00:45.280 --> 02:00:48.181
-The bid is US$ 1.950 million...
-Did you clean this?

472
02:00:48.984 --> 02:00:50.713
Who's responsibIe for...?

473
02:00:52.454 --> 02:00:56.390
Excuse me.
I have to get the last lot now.

474
02:00:56.591 --> 02:01:00.925
-What's going on?
-Sorry. but we're going to have to...

475
02:01:01.129 --> 02:01:05.156
And... sold to the lady on my left.

476
02:01:10.305 --> 02:01:13.741
-The last sale of the evening...
-Turn it on.

477
02:01:13.942 --> 02:01:16.035
Wait.

478
02:01:16.244 --> 02:01:18.337
-Where is she?
-The tag!

479
02:01:18.547 --> 02:01:23.280
...Nicolo Bussotti. 1681.
-I put the tag on myself!

480
02:01:24.252 --> 02:01:27.585
-If she would give us the pleasure.
-Too Iate.

481
02:01:29.324 --> 02:01:34.091
And here she is now. lot 72.
the so-called ''Red Violin''.

482
02:01:34.496 --> 02:01:38.125
-Here we go now.
-Call security.

483
02:01:38.333 --> 02:01:40.961
So we'll open the floor.
and who'll start us off?

484
02:01:42.037 --> 02:01:44.267
US$ 260.000! Good evening.
Mr. Ruselsky.

485
02:01:44.472 --> 02:01:46.497
US$ 270.000.
Suzanne on the telephone.

486
02:01:46.708 --> 02:01:50.872
US$ 280.000. Back to you. Sir.
US$ 300.000 at the back of the hall.

487
02:01:51.079 --> 02:01:53.445
US$ 320.000.
I see you. Suzanne.

488
02:01:53.648 --> 02:01:58.676
US$ 340. US$ 340 now in the front.
US$ 400 at the back of the hall. 420...

489
02:01:58.954 --> 02:02:01.616
500. US$ 500.000.
Against the telephone now.

490
02:02:02.324 --> 02:02:03.916
-500?
-Stop it.

491
02:02:04.125 --> 02:02:09.119
No? Against you. Sir?
US$ 600.000. US$ 700.000.

492
02:02:12.634 --> 02:02:14.295
US$ 800.000.

493
02:02:15.303 --> 02:02:17.328
US$ 900.000!

494
02:02:18.239 --> 02:02:20.935
One million dollars. Mr. Ruselsky!

495
02:02:21.176 --> 02:02:24.043
US$ 1.100 million.
US$ 1.200 million.

496
02:02:24.546 --> 02:02:26.707
Not you. Sir? Ma'am?

497
02:02:27.315 --> 02:02:30.910
-Are you sure?
-US$ 1.300 million. 1.400.

498
02:02:31.319 --> 02:02:36.052
US$ 1.400 million.
500. US$ 1.600 million.

499
02:02:40.629 --> 02:02:43.097
-Mr. Morritz?
-Down to you two now.

500
02:02:43.298 --> 02:02:44.788
US$ 2 million. Mr. Ruselsky!

501
02:02:45.467 --> 02:02:47.435
Mr. Morritz?
Mr. Morritz!

502
02:02:47.802 --> 02:02:50.965
US$ 2.100 million.
US$ 2.200 million.

503
02:02:51.406 --> 02:02:52.839
Mr. Morritz!

504
02:02:54.542 --> 02:02:58.103
Excuse me.
Is this what you're looking for?

505
02:02:58.313 --> 02:03:02.249
-Down to you two. US$ 2.200 million.
-Yes.

506
02:03:03.485 --> 02:03:05.715
-Your coat.
-US$ 2.200 million.

507
02:03:05.920 --> 02:03:08.047
US$ 2.300 million!

508
02:03:08.757 --> 02:03:10.088
US$ 2.400 million.

509
02:03:11.026 --> 02:03:12.755
Merci.

510
02:03:14.796 --> 02:03:17.822
US$ 2.400 million.

511
02:03:19.801 --> 02:03:21.769
Is that all. then?

512
02:03:23.738 --> 02:03:26.206
US$ 2.400 million.

513
02:03:33.481 --> 02:03:35.949
-You may have it.
-All done. then.

514
02:03:36.351 --> 02:03:38.683
-Are you okay. Sir?
-Yes. Take me home.

515
02:03:38.887 --> 02:03:40.514
Right away.

516
02:03:41.756 --> 02:03:47.126
Fair warning. I'm selling now
at US$ 2.400 million.

517
02:03:47.662 --> 02:03:51.530
And... sold to Mr. Ruselsky!

518
02:03:51.733 --> 02:03:53.166
Congratulations.

519
02:04:18.326 --> 02:04:20.886
Hey. baby. it's me.

520
02:04:22.630 --> 02:04:24.825
Yeah. I'm sorry.

521
02:04:25.633 --> 02:04:27.157
Yes.

522
02:04:28.269 --> 02:04:32.899
Yes. Yes. I wanted to.
every day. but...

523
02:04:33.308 --> 02:04:38.974
Well. something came up. but it's
over now. and I'm coming home.

524
02:04:41.416 --> 02:04:44.180
Oh. yeah. May I speak to her?

525
02:04:46.788 --> 02:04:49.256
Hi. honey. It's Daddy.

526
02:04:49.457 --> 02:04:51.084
How are you?

527
02:04:51.626 --> 02:04:54.322
I miss you too.

528
02:04:55.263 --> 02:04:57.231
I'm coming home.

529
02:04:57.432 --> 02:05:01.198
And honey? I'm bringing you
something very special.

530
02:05:02.305 --> 02:06:02.391
